📣 DONE is better than PERFECT 📣 It’s ok to share your progress pics. We’re our worst critics and maybe avoid posting things bc they’re not up to our standards of perfection.

My 2019 doodles weren’t bad, but I didn’t feel good about them. I had just started digital art and hadn’t found my style. Shared them anyway and got requests for pet portraits, which is how my business started!

1 year and hundreds of pet portraits later, I found my “voice.” My style hasn’t changed much since 2020 but I’ve still been making minor adjustments esp as I started drawing different animals. 

Everyone has to start somewhere and art is a never-ending journey! Don’t wait until it’s PERFECT bc it never will be 🤷🏻‍♀️

I love making these progress videos bc it’s a reminder to myself how far I’ve come + a reminder to you that everyone has to start somewhere 👏🏻

Keychain placement strategies, part 2: similarity 👯‍♀️ 

I’ve mentioned before that I don’t label my keychains with breed names. As a result, the designs are open for interpretation and people often buy designs that aren’t meant for their breed, especially if the markings work better. I like to place similar designs near each other to nudge them in the right direction 😉

Examples shown in this video 👇🏻
- Chihuahuas, chiweenies, basenjis, bull terriers
- Bichon, coton de tulear, American eskimo
- Cavalier King Charles spaniel, cocker spaniel, Brittany spaniel 

Believe it or not, a lot of thought went into the placement of each keychain. I didn’t just throw everything into the wall. And bc I felt like it’d be a waste to not share, I’m revealing my thoughts and secrets in these videos. Hope it helps you with product placement in your booth!

Keychain placement strategies, part 3: no line breaks 💔

It was like putting together a puzzle, but I made sure all the colors of the same breed fit on the same line. I think it’s much easier to browse this way because there’s often a crowd in front of the panel, so designs on the next line might be missed. 

Examples shown in this video 👇🏻
- Frenchies
- Doberman, German pinschers/min pins

TRIPLE MY SALES PT 4: sticker display 📈💪🏻 Don’t make the same mistake I did!

I didn’t want to invest in my setup early on bc I was afraid of “wasting” money… until I started seeing those investments as a way to increase return.

Ways I improved my sticker setup over time:
- Added labels and organizing alphabetically by breed
- Placee sample stickers on the backs of the bins so it’s easier to find things, the design shows even if something sells out, indicates there’s multiple colors in each bin, and makes the box look fuller.

These were small changes, but I saw a huge increase in my sticker sales! So, take it from me: don’t be afraid to try new things and invest a bit to grow. You gotta spend money to make money!

Don’t give up on your dreams! You never know what’s waiting right around the corner 🥺

In 2019, I knew I wanted to pursue something creative. I took on ANY creative job I could find, from branding to mural painting to product design. My income was unstable and unreliable, but I made it work. Towards the end of the year, I started offering pet portraits and that was the turning point for me. I found my ikigai!

Fast forward to 2023—I’m now running a pet art business and I get to be my own boss! 👏🏻 I share my experiences on social media hoping to help other aspiring creatives who felt lost like 2019 me ♡

This was my highest income month ever 😳 Let’s go over my income streams this month 👇🏻

Aff 🔗s - Not huge earnings, but buys me a few coffees ☕️ I have all my small biz essentials listed in my b!o and I make a small commission every time someone buys something on it. I only share things I personally use!

Online - My online sales have been consistently 5 figures every month and increasing steadily. I actually think this number could have been higher but a lot of things were out of stock bc of market season. Still experiencing some growing pains here!

Events - I did 3 really successful events by 626 Night Market and Foodieland. 1 day at another event fell on the last day of the month so I included sales from that day here. I broke a lot of records this year so it’s much higher than I expected! I have vendor vlogs of each event if you wanna know the deets on each one 🎬

DISCLAIMERS ⚠️

All processing fees, shipping, and sales tax have been removed from these numbers. This is what actually went into my bank BEFORE certain expenses (see below) and income tax.

For monthly recurring expenses, see my March income video. It is almost the same every month other than production costs, which I do not disclose to protect my business. Please don’t ask about that or my manufacturing info.

I am not looking for financial advice and I am not qualified to offer advice either. I just share personal experiences in hopes of helping other aspiring artists and small biz owners.

This did not happen overnight. This is the result of YEARS of hard work. I am so so grateful I get to do what I love. Thank you for supporting my little pet art biz 💕

One of the most frustrating things about creating dog designs is that I can’t win. 

I follow breed standards but then I’m leaving out mixed breeds, rescues, and uncommon colors that deserve representation! But the moment I release designs for those of standard pups, I’m as unethical and immoral as a backyard breeder.

Let me just remind you that I’m creating keychains and stickers, not actual animals! 📣

One of my BIGGEST secrets to Etsy success is catering to NICHES. In my case, that’s exotic pets, mixed breeds, and of standard colors.

Since those uncommon animals have less representation, there’s less competition and my shop will show up higher in the results—remember, Etsy is a search engine.

Making sales boosts your ranking on Etsy! When you make sales on niche products, your other items will be bumped up too, making your shop more discoverable overall.

If there’s a hole in the market, fill it! Don’t forget the niches 👏🏻

These are my PERSONAL experiences. Please don’t let my opinions discourage you from trying them out for yourself! 

#smallbusiness #popupshop #petexpo #dogshow #reptileshow #birdshow #catcon #vendor #boothdisplay #keychain #stickershop

I’ve mentioned my bad experiences at dog shows here and there, but never fully disclosed the unsolicited “advice” I got at them. I do get criticism about my mixed breed designs online but it hit so much harder hearing those comments in person, especially as a newbie vendor!!

Cherry on top had to be the person who left me their business card at the end and said I could reach out for advice on which breeds/colors I need to discontinue 💀

Yeah, don’t miss that crowd at all 🫣
